.\" Manpage for local-mark
.\" Generated from local-mark project
.\"
.TH LOCAL-MARK 1 "July 2026" "local-mark 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
local-mark \- Local-first bookmark browser with embedded SPA and multi-database support
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B local-mark
[\fIOPTION\fR]... \fIFILE\fR [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B local-mark
is a local-first bookmark browser. It reads one or more JSON bookmark databases
(created with \fBmarks2json\fR(1)) and serves an embedded single-page application
(SPA) over HTTP. The frontend provides browsing, search, tag filtering, random
link picking, database statistics, and a multi-database selector.

All static assets (HTML, JavaScript, CSS, favicon, service worker) are
gzip-compressed and embedded directly into the binary at compile time. No
filesystem access is required at runtime for frontend assets.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Display help and exit.
.TP
\fB-V\fR, \fB--version\fRk
Print version and exit.
.TP
\fB--usage\fR
Display brief usage summary.
.PP
Logging:
.TP
\fB-L\fR, \fB--log-level\fR=\fILEVEL\fR
Set log level: \fIerror\fR, \fIwarn\fR, \fIinfo\fR (default), \fIdebug\fR.
.TP
\fB-F\fR, \fB--log-file\fR=\fIFILE\fR
Append logs to \fIFILE\fR instead of stderr.
.TP
\fB-R\fR, \fB--print-request\fR
Log each client request with headers (verbose).
.PP
Authentication:
.TP
\fB-u\fR, \fB--user\fR=\fIUSER\fR
Enable HTTP Basic Authentication with username \fIUSER\fR.
.TP
\fB-p\fR, \fB--pass\fR=\fIPASS\fR
Enable HTTP Basic Authentication with password \fIPASS\fR.
(Requires \fB--user\fR.)
.PP
Connection:
.TP
\fB-H\fR, \fB--host\fR=\fIHOST\fR
Bind address (default: \fBlocalhost\fR). Use \fB0.0.0.0\fR for all interfaces.
.TP
\fB-P\fR, \fB--port\fR=\fIPORT\fR
TCP port to listen on (default: \fB8080\fR).
.TP
\fB-T\fR, \fB--threads\fR=\fINUM\fR
Thread pool size (default: \fB2\fR, range: \fB1-256\fR).
.TP
\fB-K\fR, \fB--keep-alive\fR=\fISECS\fR
Keep-alive timeout in seconds (default: \fB3\fR, \fB0\fR = disable).
.TP
\fB-M\fR, \fB--max-conns\fR=\fINUM\fR
Max concurrent connections per IP (default: \fB0\fR = unlimited, range: \fB0-1000\fR).
.PP
Browser:
.TP
\fB-B\fR, \fB--browser\fR=\fIBROWSER\fR
Open \fIBROWSER\fR on startup (e.g., \fBfirefox\fR, \fBchrome\fR, \fBopen\fR on macOS).
.PP
Positional arguments:
.TP
\fIFILE\fR...
Bookmark JSON database file(s) (max 10). At least one required.
.SH FILES
The JSON database files must follow the schema produced by \fBmarks2json\fR(1):
.PP
.nf
{
  "book_Marks": [
    {
      "category": "Category Name",
      "bookmarks": [
        {
          "title": "Display Title",
          "url": "https://example.com",
          "description": "Optional description",
          "tags": ["#tag1", "#tag2"],
          "domain": "example.com",
          "icon": "https://..."   // YouTube channels only
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "book_mark_domain_hash": { "example.com": 42 },
  "book_mark_tag_hash": { "#tag1": 10, "#tag2": 5 }
}
.fi
.PP
Categories are derived from filenames by \fBmarks2json\fR(1).
.SH API ENDPOINTS
.TP
\fBGET /bookmarks.json\fR
First database (backward compatibility).
.TP
\fBGET /bookmarks/<idx>.json\fR
Database at index \fIidx\fR (0-based, matches CLI argument order).
.TP
\fBGET /api/databases\fR
List all databases with metadata (name, path, size, mtime, permissions, owner/group).
.TP
\fBGET /api/databases/<idx>\fR
Metadata for single database.
.TP
\fBGET /*\fR
Embedded frontend assets (index.html, JS, CSS, favicon, sw.js).
All served from memory with ETag, Range, and gzip support.
.SH FRONTEND FEATURES
.TP
Database Selector (\fB#databases\fR)
Landing page showing all databases as cards with metadata.
Click a card to select; choice persisted in \fBlocalStorage\fR.
.TP
Browse View (\fB#browse\fR)
Sidebar with categories (and Favorites), search (\fB/\fR), tag pills,
layout toggle (single/grid/compact), resizable sidebar, keyboard navigation.
.TP
Info View (\fB#info\fR)
Statistics, category bar chart, tag cloud, domain grid, link health checker.
.TP
Random View (\fB#random\fR)
Pick N random links with optional category/tag filters; "Open All".
.TP
Theming
Dark (default) and light themes via CSS variables.
Auto-detects \fBprefers-color-scheme\fR; manual toggle persists to \fBlocalStorage\fR.
.TP
Persistence
\fBlocalStorage\fR keys: \fBlocalmarks-active-db\fR, \fBlocalmarks-favorites\fR,
\fBlocalmarks-layout\fR, \fBlocalmarks-sidebar-w\fR, \fBlocalmarks-theme\fR.
\fBIndexedDB\fR cache (\fBLocalMarksCache\fR) for offline/stale-while-revalidate.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS (Browse View)
.nf
  j / DOWN_ARROW   Next bookmark
  k / UP_ARROW     Previous bookmark
  h / LEFT_ARROW   Back to categories (sidebar)
  l / RIGHT_ARROW  Into bookmarks (cards)
  gg               Jump to first
  G                Jump to last
  /                Focus search
  Enter            Open in new tab
  o                Open in same tab
  yy               Copy URL (domain toast)
  p                Toggle pin/favorite
  Esc              Clear search / close help
  ?                Toggle help modal
  Ctrl/Cmd+K       Focus search
.fi
